org.sbml.squeezer

Class ParameterFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.squeezer.ParameterFactory

  • public class ParameterFactory
extends Object
    This class has many factory methods for the creation of parameters to be used in varous kinetic equations for a specific model. (2010-10-22)
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger, Sarah R. Müller vom Hagen

      • createOrGetGlobalParameter

        public org.sbml.jsbml.Parameter createOrGetGlobalParameter(String id)
        If the parent model does not yet contain a parameter with the given id, a new parameter is created, its value is set to 1 and it is added to the list of global parameters in the model. If there is already a parameter with this id, a reference to it will be returned.
        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the global parameter.

      • createOrGetParameter

        public org.sbml.jsbml.LocalParameter createOrGetParameter(Object... idParts)
        Equivalent to createOrGetParameter(java.lang.Object...) but the parts of the id can be given separately to this method and are concatenated.
        Parameters:
        idParts -
        Returns:

      • createOrGetParameter

        public org.sbml.jsbml.LocalParameter createOrGetParameter(String id)
        If a Parameter with the given identifier has already been created and is contained in the list of LocalParameters for this KineticLaw, a pointer to it will be returned. If no such Parameter exists, a new Parameter with the default value will be created and a pointer to it will be returned.
        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the local parameter.
        Returns:
